Very good family run, neighborhood sandwich shop featuring house made corned beef and homemade soups. I stopped in on a cold rainy October day and ordered a Pastrami sandwich with brown mustard and melted Swiss cheese. Normally the sandwich comes with a dill coleslaw, which I asked to not have on the sandwich. The pastrami was perfectly thin and delicious. But the homemade soup really hit the spot with hand cut veggies, chicken, noodles, and a perfectly seasoned tomato based broth. It was delicious and perfect for a rainy afternoon.

It's a good sandwich spot. The owner is a great guy, easy to talk to while your food is being prepared. They have some pretty unique stuff here, but in the end, it's an old fashioned deli. Nothing too special. Solid deli sandwiches. I'll be back.

This cash only deli/sando shop/beer stop/convenience store makes me said I don't live in the hood any longer. I've never lived in New York, but in my imagination Harry and Sally and Seinfeld and Kramer and Nora Ephron are all about to walk into their door to order their regular. The place has soul, as well as some killer sandwiches. Order yourself the RJ, which includes pepper jack cheese, onions, turkey, and pastrami. Then walk over and drink a can of Dr. Brown's while they're assembling your sandwich on that divine french bread. If you're smart, you'll get yourself a 6 pack of local beer and some pastrami, as well as some salt and vinegar chips on your way out. Slightly pricey, yes— but worth every penny. Plus, the sandos are so big you'll have half for later. FTR, Cash only, so hit that atm.
The real deal. Get the R.J.
Love the Macy's Parade Sandwich - turkey, havarti, cranberry sauce & bacon.  Tastes like the morning after thanksgiving! FYI - they are cash only and they deliver beer!
